{"name":"Talents","permission":{"default":0,"Sd8TaawsSgOTEPU7":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.R4ZTXOGbs2kGPhMw"}},"content":"<h1>Talents</h1>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue';\">Talents are by fare the most advanced in the system. It more or less effects everything else in the system.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue';\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue';\">Figure 1: An example of a talent</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue';\"><img src=\"https://i.ibb.co/x6tbKLj/Screenshot-2021-02-19-at-13-42-24.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"530\" height=\"1173\" /></p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue';\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 6px; color: #191813; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">The sheet consists of the following fields:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul1\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: medium;\">\n<li class=\"li2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">An Image<br /><br /></li>\n<li class=\"li2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Name of the Talent<br /><br /></li>\n<li class=\"li2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Below the name is a label that tells you that Item type this is.&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\n<li class=\"li2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Talent groupname: On the Talent page of an actor sheet this represents the grouping name.<br /><br /></li>\n<li class=\"li2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; color: #1b1f22;\">Uses: If the talent has the limited number of uses they can be recorded in this section; Uses - is the current number of times the talent has been used. Max - Maximum number of uses for talent.<br /><br /></p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; color: #131310;\">Attack Roll Bonuses: Everything effecting you attack roll.<br />Boons/Banes: Do you get a boon or bane bonus to your attack roll.<br />Attributes: What attributes are effected by a boon/bane.<br />Damage: Do you get a damage bonus from this talent.<br />Extra Damage: Do you get an extra damage bonus from this talent if your roll is 20+.<br />Extra Effects: A description of the extra effect. Printed out in the chat window.<br /><br /></li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; color: #131310;\">Challenge Roll: Boons/Banes bonuses<br />Sometimes certain attributes get boons/banes bonuses.<br /><br /></li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; color: #131310;\"><span style=\"color: #131310; font-family: Helvetica;\">VS Roll: Sometimes a talent requires you to&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: #131310; font-family: Helvetica;\">succeed on an attribute roll versus an opponent attribute.</span><br />\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; color: #15171a;\">Usually the roll is made with a boons/banes bonuses.<br />The outcome can be some type of damage. You can add multiple types of damage. Damage from a bite and 1d6 of poison etc.<br /><br /></p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; color: #131310;\">Healing: The talent can heal and show the option in the char window.<br /><br /></li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; color: #131310;\">Make a damage roll: The talent just do damage.<br /><br /></li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; color: #131310;\">Add bonuses to your characteristics: Simply add a flat bonus to one or more characteristics.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Figure 2: Example an attack in char window with multiple talents activated</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.ibb.co/MgX8smJ/Screenshot-2021-02-19-at-14-30-37.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"267\" height=\"372\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; color: #15171a;\">The system tries to&nbsp;figure out that talents are currently effecting what you are doing. Boons and banes cancels each other out.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span></p>","_id":"7nmDaG2hCEhnnvpK"}
{"name":"Tab: Talents","permission":{"default":0,"Sd8TaawsSgOTEPU7":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.TUt6f9tFrUX1F5WQ"}},"content":"<h1>Tab: Talents</h1>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 7px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\">The Talents tab shows all your Talents from your Ancestry and Paths.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 7px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\">You have to create those talents yourself with data from the Core Rules.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 7px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Figure 1: Talents Tab</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.ibb.co/MM2wthb/Screenshot-2021-02-19-at-13-55-03.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"510\" height=\"394\" /></p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 7px; color: #191813; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 6px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; color: #131310;\">The page consists of the following fields:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul1\" style=\"font-size: medium;\">\n<li class=\"li2\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; color: #131310;\">A group name. Simply to group your talents in paths.</li>\n<li class=\"li2\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; color: #131310;\">An Image</li>\n<li class=\"li2\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; color: #131310;\">Title of the talent (click to show or roll it)</li>\n<li class=\"li2\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; color: #131310;\">Below the title is a button to show a quick overview of the talent.</li>\n<li class=\"li2\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; color: #131310;\">Uses: Some talents can only be used a number of times pr. day.</li>\n<li class=\"li2\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; color: #131310;\">Activate/Deactivate talent. Meaning if activated you gain the benefits from the talent. Bonuses and rolls are effected.</li>\n<li class=\"li2\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; color: #131310;\">Edit Talent</li>\n<li class=\"li2\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; color: #131310;\">Delete Talent</li>\n</ul>","_id":"MzYKFxArNqAu42sW"}
{"name":"Paths","permission":{"default":0,"Sd8TaawsSgOTEPU7":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.FIPYDwvW9Jwcyd8N"}},"content":"<h1>Paths</h1>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; color: #15171a;\">Everything on a path is automatically transferred to the character sheet. You as a player only need to mark which attributes you want to increase. An exception is paths like the Rogue where you need to make a choice regarding Roguery Talents. You have to select the one you want and click the transfer button to add it to your character sheet.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; color: #15171a;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; color: #15171a;\">Figure 1: A path in view mode</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.ibb.co/mJBdQDn/Screenshot-2021-02-19-at-14-38-11.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"429\" height=\"740\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; color: #15171a;\">Figure 2: A path in edit mode<br /><img src=\"https://i.ibb.co/GTSP5vm/Screenshot-2021-02-19-at-14-38-33.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"429\" height=\"579\" /><br /><br /></p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 6px; color: #191813; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">The sheet consists of the following fields:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul1\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: medium;\">\n<li class=\"li2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">An Image<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" /><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" /></li>\n<li class=\"li2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Name of the Talent<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" /><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" /></li>\n<li class=\"li2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Below the name is a label that tells you that Item type this is.&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\n<li class=\"li2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Path Type: Novice, Expert or Master<br /><br /></li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; color: #131310;\">A list of levels. Each level look like the one in figure 2. There is a button to the right that allows you to add a level to a path.<br /><br /></li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; color: #131310;\">Level: Enter what level this is.<br /><br /></li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; color: #10100e;\">Attributes: Choose what type of attribute advancement you need for this path.<br />Enter the value you gain by selecting the attributes.<br /><br /></li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; color: #131310;\">Characteristics: The level bonus on each characteristics.<br /><br /></li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; color: #131310;\">Languages and Professions: Write whatever the Core Rules are saying.<br /><br /></li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; color: #10100e;\">Equipment: Some SotDL supplements&nbsp;grants you some starting equipment.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;<br /><br /></span></li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; color: #10100e;\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">Magic: Just write that the Core Rules are saying.<br /><br /></span></li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; color: #0e0e0d;\">Talents: The dotted lines are a drop zone and when you drag/drop a talent on it it&rsquo;s stored on the path.</li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; color: #0e0e0d;\">Talents (choose one): Works the way talents does.&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; color: #0e0e0d;\">Spells: Works the same way as talents does except it's spells you add.</li>\n</ul>","_id":"N8H9cpsxVdVJsG7g"}
{"name":"Character Sheet","permission":{"default":0,"Sd8TaawsSgOTEPU7":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.9uhF63XMIgNmaYk5"}},"content":"<h1>Character Sheet</h1>\n<p>Figure 1: Character Sheet</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.ibb.co/kDD5Syc/character-sheet.webp\" alt=\"Character Sheet\" width=\"700\" height=\"661\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ol class=\"ol1\" style=\"font-size: medium;\">\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\"><strong>Characters name</strong><br /><br /></li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\"><strong>Level</strong><br />When updating this field it triggers certain fields to update on the character sheet. So you have to change your level to gain the perks from your Ancestry and Paths.<br /><br />\n<ul>\n<li>Ancestry: On level 4 it automatically increase you total health by the number written.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Paths: It automatically adds Health, Talents and Spells that matches your current level and below.<br /><br /></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\"><strong>Attributes</strong><br />Determined by your Ancestry and Paths.<br /><br />The large circle represents the value of your attribute the smaller number in the top right is your modifier that will be added to your rolls.<br /><br />Perception: Is derived from Intellect and is automatically calculated.<br /><br />🎲 Clicking on the attribute name allows you to make a challenge roll.<br /><br /></li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\"><strong>Characteristics</strong><br />All except for Fortune is automatically calculated and they too are based on your Ancestry and Paths.<br /><br />Damage, Insanity and Corruption are represented by a bar.<br />Left-clicked on the title/label to increase the value and Right-clicked to decrease in value. Alternatively, click the edit button (square+pencil icon) and you can manually type in the value.<br /><br />\n<ul>\n<li>Defense: Is calculated based on your agility, ancestry, paths and armor.</li>\n<li>Power: Can be changed on your ancestry.</li>\n<li>Size and Speed: Are values from your ancestry.</li>\n<li>Healing Rate: Calculated from your ancestry and total health.<br />Injured: A checkmark box.</li>\n<li>Fast/Slow Turn: A button to toggle your fast/slow turn order.<br /><br /></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\"><strong>Character Info</strong><br />General fields to describe your characters looks.<br /><br />\n<ul>\n<li>Ancestry: When you drag and drop an Ancestry Item onto the character sheet it&rsquo;ll show up here.<br /><br />When a plus icon is shown in the fields, you can create a blank Ancestry and fill in the blanks. Usually you don&rsquo;t do this. The GM creates Ancestry item that you can drag/drop onto your character sheet. They are predefined with the values you need.<br /><br />When an edit button is shown, you can click to show and edit the Ancestry item. This will be covered in further detail in the Ancestries journal entry.<br /><br />@JournalEntry[woNOPU8AlflnL338]{Ancestries}<br /><br /></li>\n<li>Religion: You can enter a text and choose an image to represent your religious believes.<br /><br /></li>\n<li>Languages: A list of languages known to the character.<br />The system comes with a set of language items. You can import them and drag/drop them unto the character sheet. Starting languages is part of your ancestry and will automatically be added when an ancestry is chosen. This will be covered in further detail in the Ancestry journal entry.<br /><br />You can click on the edit button to edit your languages. Trashcan to delete or select the R/W/S (Read/Write/Spoken) characters to toggle on/off.<br /><strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><br /><img src=\"https://i.ibb.co/Jx0RPDf/Screenshot-2021-02-18-at-13-13-18.webp\" alt=\"Languages\" width=\"394\" height=\"124\" /><br /><br /></span></span></strong></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\"><strong>Paths</strong><br />When a Path item is dragged/dropped onto your character sheet they will show up here and an edit button is shown.<br /><br />Paths will be covered in further detail in the Paths journal entry.<br /><br /></li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\"><strong>Professions</strong><br />Drag and drop your Profession items or create your own.<br /><br /></li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\"><strong>Features</strong><br />Drag and drop your Feature items or create your own.<br /><br /></li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\"><strong>Character image</strong><br />Click on the image to choose an image for your character.<br /><br /></li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\"><strong>Toggle PC/NPC</strong><br />A botton to toggle between PC or an NPC sheet. Right now it only changes the image frame and the sidebar graphics. See Figure 2.<br /><br /></li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\"><strong>Character Mods</strong><br />A separate popup window where you can set Afflictions and add modifiers if you are effected by a spell. This will be covered in further detail in the Character Mod journal entry.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><br /><br /></p>\n<p>Figure 2: NPC Character Sheet</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.ibb.co/2Nsvk49/character-sheet-npc.webp\" alt=\"NPC Character Sheet\" width=\"700\" height=\"656\" /></p>","img":"","_id":"SNaZuDLPs3AolJKN"}
{"name":"Tab: Combat","permission":{"default":0,"Sd8TaawsSgOTEPU7":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.pyvEu9Yqudn8a9Ob"}},"content":"<h1>Tab: Combat</h1>\n<p><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Helvetica;\">Figuer 1: Combat Tab</span></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.ibb.co/tz5V6hp/Screenshot-2021-02-18-at-13-38-51.webp\" alt=\"Combat Tab\" width=\"600\" height=\"437\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 7px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">The combat tab shows all your weapons, armor, shield and ammunition.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 7px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">All weapons, armors, shield and ammunition from the Core Rules is part of the system and can be found under compendiums. Just drag/drop them onto your character sheet.<br /><br /></p>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"p1\" style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Weapons:&nbsp;Image, Weapon name and any requirements and properties is listed below. Damage and Banes/Boons are also shown.<br /><br />They're 3 button to the right. Equip, Edit and Delete. If a weapon or an armor is equip and you don&rsquo;t meet the requirements the icon turns red and the system automatically adds the penalties.<br /><br /><span style=\"color: #131310; font-family: 'Apple Color Emoji';\">🎲</span><span class=\"s1\" style=\"color: #131310; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal;\">&nbsp;By clicking on the weapons name you can make an Attack roll.<br /><br /></span></li>\n<li class=\"p1\" style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Armor: Any bonuses to defense is automatically added when equipped.<br /><br /></li>\n<li class=\"p1\" style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Ammunition: You can left-click on the amount number to increase and right-click to decrease.</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 7px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Edit Weapon</h2>\n<p>Figure 2: Edit weapon<br /><img src=\"https://i.ibb.co/zPrwNHn/Screenshot-2021-02-18-at-13-59-27.webp\" alt=\"Edit Weapon\" width=\"600\" height=\"659\" /><br /><br /></p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Sometimes you need to choose with Attack Modifer you want to use. The the weapon has a Swift property you can choose between Strength or Agilty as a modifier to your attack roll.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica;\">You can add multiple damage and damage types if need.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica;\">E.g. if a weapon has an extra 1d6 Fire damage from a spell. It will be shown as different types of damage and damage is rolled separately.</span></p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 36px; text-indent: -36px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Everything combat related will be covered in further detail in the Combat journal entry.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 36px; text-indent: -36px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 36px; text-indent: -36px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; text-indent: -36px;\">@JournalEntry[ZF3hE21DjzP8j9OO]{Combat}&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 36px; text-indent: -36px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">&nbsp;</p>","_id":"jlFjtjCciMBZvCfh"}
{"name":"Ancestries","permission":{"default":0,"Sd8TaawsSgOTEPU7":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.woNOPU8AlflnL338"}},"content":"<h1>Ancestries</h1>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 6px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">The sheet consists of the following fields:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul1\" style=\"font-size: medium;\">\n<li class=\"li2\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">An Image (images for Ancestries are included&nbsp;in the system)</li>\n<li class=\"li2\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Name of the Ancestry</li>\n<li class=\"li2\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Below the name is a label that tells you that Item type this is.&nbsp;</li>\n<li class=\"li2\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">A toggle button to view it in edit mode or in view mode. The view mode is what the players will see.</li>\n<li class=\"li2\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Starting Attributes.&nbsp;</li>\n<li class=\"li2\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Characteristics</li>\n<li class=\"li2\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Languages</li>\n<li class=\"li2\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Talents</li>\n<li class=\"li2\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Level 4: Health</li>\n<li class=\"li2\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Level 4: Options</li>\n<li class=\"li2\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Level 4: Talents</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 6px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 6px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">You'll need the Core Rules to fill in the fields for each Ancestry.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 6px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Everything updates the character sheet except Insanity, Corruption, and the option you choose at level 4. If you pick a Talent you have to manually transfer it to your character sheet.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 6px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 7px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">The grey dotted areas are drop zones. You drag/drop languages and talents onto these areas.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 7px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">A set of languages is provided with the system and you just have to drag them in from the compendium.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 7px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Regarding Talents you have to create those yourself.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Figure 1: Example of an Ancestry</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.ibb.co/Gnk9nj3/Screenshot-2021-02-19-at-10-57-55.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"525\" height=\"994\" /></p>","_id":"kvoHFTm3wINamWr8"}
{"name":"Combat","permission":{"default":0,"Sd8TaawsSgOTEPU7":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.ZF3hE21DjzP8j9OO"}},"content":"<h1>Combat</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2 class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica;\">Chat: Attack roll</span></h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica;\"><span style=\"font-family: Signika, sans-serif;\">Figure 2: Attack roll modifer</span></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica;\"><img style=\"font-family: Signika, sans-serif;\" src=\"https://i.ibb.co/dmGj5Q8/Screenshot-2021-02-18-at-14-19-37.webp\" alt=\"Attack roll in chat\" width=\"391\" height=\"97\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 7px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica;\">When you click to make an Attack roll it shows a dialog where you can add Banes and Boons to your roll. Your GM will tell you if and how many to add. Boons are a positive number and Banes a negative. Each Boon/Bane will add an extra d6 to your roll.&nbsp;</span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica;\">Boon: The dice with the highest number will be added to your roll.&nbsp;</span><br /><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica;\">Bane: The dice with the highest number will be subtracted&nbsp;from your roll.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica;\"><span style=\"font-family: Signika, sans-serif;\">Figure 3: Attack roll in chat</span></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica;\"><img src=\"https://i.ibb.co/QmdftH5/Screenshot-2021-02-18-at-14-30-08.webp\" alt=\"Attack roll in chat\" width=\"300\" height=\"194\" /></span></p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">The chat shows:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul1\" style=\"font-size: medium;\">\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">The characters name</li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Ancestry</li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">The characters highest Path</li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">An image of the weapon used</li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Name of the weapon</li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Name of a taget if selected</li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">The attribute use in the attack</li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">The defense of a choosen target if a target is slected.</li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">A button to roll damage.</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Signika, sans-serif;\">Figure 4: Attack troll in chat with talents active</span></p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal;\"><img src=\"https://i.ibb.co/bbxHtpW/Screenshot-2021-02-18-at-14-45-32.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"304\" height=\"368\" /></p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 36px; text-indent: -36px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">An advanced example:</p>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"p1\" style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica;\">Hover on Attack roll shows the dice rolled. d20 + Strength modifer + 1 Boon (if multiple the highest is selected).</span></li>\n<li class=\"p1\" style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica;\">A list of all effects (talents) active for this attack. 1 Boon to attack. Extra damage +1d6 and an extra 1d6 if roll is above 20+.</span></li>\n<li class=\"p1\" style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica;\">Two buttons for damage rolls.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica;\">Support for using the Foundry Target system and if one don't want to use it.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica;\">Chat: Creature rolls</span></h3>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">By default only the GM sees the attack result and Defense (target number) value of the creature. The roll is not shown and the players can't hover over the result and see the modifiers of the creature.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">This can be changed in the System setttings.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\"><span style=\"font-family: Signika, sans-serif;\">Figure 5: System settings</span></p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\"><img src=\"https://i.ibb.co/LtPBRnS/Screenshot-2021-02-19-at-10-05-46.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"561\" height=\"91\" /></p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">&nbsp;</p>","_id":"rXr3yRgj8MjwZ4rg"}
{"name":"Making a Character","permission":{"default":0,"Sd8TaawsSgOTEPU7":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.Wbru0A8EcoHrVFNh"}},"content":"<h1>Making a Character</h1>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">First get familiar with the layout of the character sheet.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"p1\" style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">@JournalEntry[9uhF63XMIgNmaYk5]{Character Sheet}</li>\n<li class=\"p1\" style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">@JournalEntry[pyvEu9Yqudn8a9Ob]{Tab: Combat}</li>\n<li class=\"p1\" style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">@JournalEntry[TUt6f9tFrUX1F5WQ]{Tab: Talents}</li>\n<li class=\"p1\" style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Tab: Magic</li>\n<li class=\"p1\" style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Tab: Inventory</li>\n<li class=\"p1\" style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Tab: Background</li>\n<li class=\"p1\" style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Actor Mods</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Prerequisites</h2>\n<p>Buy the Core Rules book. You can't play the game without the rules.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>To get the character sheet working, you'll need to create a few things first:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Ancestries</li>\n<li>Paths</li>\n<li>Talents</li>\n<li>Spells (if you need any)</li>\n</ol>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3><strong>Ancestries</strong></h3>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">There are 6 ancestries in the Core Rules. I'll recommend just creating them all from the beginning.</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[woNOPU8AlflnL338]{Ancestries}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3><strong>Paths</strong></h3>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">There are 4 Novice Paths, 16 Expert Paths and 64 Master Paths in the Core Rules.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Only create the Paths and their Talents you need. There&rsquo;s a staggering amount of content in the book and most of them you&rsquo;ll never use anyway. Slowly expand with what you need over time.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">@JournalEntry[FIPYDwvW9Jwcyd8N]{Paths}</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\"><strong>Spells</strong></h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica;\">There are 30 Traditions of magic in the Core Rules.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">I'll recommend the same approach as with Paths, only create those you need.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Fill out your character sheet</h2>\n<ol>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Level: Set the starting level for your character.<br /><br /></li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Ancestry: Choose an Ancestry from the list the GM has made and drag/drop it onto your character sheet.<br /><br />Edit you Ancestry and adjust your Starting Attributes according to the rules.<br /><br /></li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Paths: If you start at level 1 or higher. Drag/drop a Path onto your character sheet. <br />Edit you paths and choose your attribute increases. Attributes, Characteristics, Talents and Spells will automatically be transferred to your character sheet. Some paths like the Rogue has to make some chooses on certain levels. Those chooses of Talents you have to transfer yourself.<br /><br /></li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Professions: Create them on the character sheet<br /><br /></li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Features: Are optional. I use them to write down Changeling Quirks, Clockwork Form, Appearance and Personality.<br /><br /></li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Inventory: Enter your wealth and add your starting items.<br /><br /></li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica;\">Religion: Write the name of your religion/belief&nbsp;and optional choose an image.</span><br /><br /></li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Languages: Check them to see if they are correct.<br /><br /></li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Image: Select an image for your character.<br /><br /></li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Weapons: Drag/drop Weapons, Armor, Shield and Ammunition from the compendiums onto the character sheet.<br /><br /></li>\n<li class=\"li1\" style=\"margin: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Background: Write something cool.</li>\n</ol>","_id":"wp0RvhTTkxhIu5W1"}
